Subject: [PATCH] unopy __init__: skip add_dll_directory when unopy.libs absent

The unopy.libs/ directory is created by delvewheel (or equivalent) when
producing a self-contained PyPI wheel — it does not exist in source
installs or in conda-forge builds where runtime DLLs live in the env's
Library/bin (already added to the DLL search path by conda's activation
script). Unconditionally calling os.add_dll_directory on the missing path
raises FileNotFoundError at import time.

Guard the Windows branch on the directory's existence so source/conda
installs work while wheel installs are unaffected.

diff --git interfaces/Python/unopy/__init__.py interfaces/Python/unopy/__init__.py
index 21ae231..1033e3d 100644
--- interfaces/Python/unopy/__init__.py
+++ interfaces/Python/unopy/__init__.py
@@ -4,7 +4,7 @@ import sys
 # load bundled DLLs from unopy.libs
 basedir = os.path.dirname(__file__)
 subdir = os.path.join(basedir, '..', 'unopy.libs')
-if os.name == 'nt':
+if os.name == 'nt' and os.path.isdir(subdir):
     # Prepend to PATH so our DLLs are found before any system MinGW ones
     os.environ['PATH'] = subdir + os.pathsep + os.environ.get('PATH', '')
     os.add_dll_directory(subdir)
